.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::Nutzap \- NIP\-61 nutzaps (Cashu ecash payments)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::Nutzap;
\&
\&    my $pubkey      = \*(Aqaa\*(Aq x 32;
\&    my $p2pk_pubkey = \*(Aqcc\*(Aq x 32;
\&
\&    # Publish nutzap info (kind 10019) \- tells others how to send you ecash
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Nutzap\->info_event(
\&        pubkey      => $pubkey,
\&        relays      => [\*(Aqwss://relay1\*(Aq, \*(Aqwss://relay2\*(Aq],
\&        mints       => [
\&            { url => \*(Aqhttps://mint1\*(Aq, units => [\*(Aqusd\*(Aq, \*(Aqsat\*(Aq] },
\&            { url => \*(Aqhttps://mint2\*(Aq, units => [\*(Aqsat\*(Aq] },
\&        ],
\&        p2pk_pubkey => $p2pk_pubkey,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Send a nutzap (kind 9321)
\&    my $proof_json = \*(Aq{"amount":1,"C":"02...","id":"000a","secret":"..."}\*(Aq;
\&    my $zap = Net::Nostr::Nutzap\->nutzap(
\&        pubkey     => $pubkey,
\&        recipient  => \*(Aqbb\*(Aq x 32,
\&        proofs     => [$proof_json],
\&        mint_url   => \*(Aqhttps://mint1\*(Aq,
\&        unit       => \*(Aqsat\*(Aq,
\&        event_id   => \*(Aqdd\*(Aq x 32,
\&        event_kind => \*(Aq1\*(Aq,
\&        content    => \*(AqGreat post!\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Record redemption (kind 7376)
\&    my $nutzap_event_id = \*(Aqee\*(Aq x 32;
\&    my $redeem = Net::Nostr::Nutzap\->redemption(
\&        pubkey        => $pubkey,
\&        nutzap_ids    => [$nutzap_event_id],
\&        sender_pubkey => \*(Aqbb\*(Aq x 32,
\&        relay_hint    => \*(Aqwss://relay1\*(Aq,
\&        content       => $encrypted_content,  # NIP\-44 encrypted
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse any nutzap\-related event
\&    my $parsed = Net::Nostr::Nutzap\->from_event($event);
\&
\&    # Validate
\&    Net::Nostr::Nutzap\->validate($event);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-61 nutzaps \-\- peer\-to\-peer Cashu ecash payments over Nostr.
A nutzap is a P2PK\-locked Cashu token where the payment itself is the
receipt.
.PP
Three event kinds are involved:
.IP "\fBkind 10019\fR \- Nutzap informational event (replaceable). Lists the user\*(Aqs trusted mints, relay preferences, and P2PK public key for receiving nutzaps. The P2PK pubkey MUST NOT be the user\*(Aqs main Nostr public key." 4
.IX Item "kind 10019 - Nutzap informational event (replaceable). Lists the user's trusted mints, relay preferences, and P2PK public key for receiving nutzaps. The P2PK pubkey MUST NOT be the user's main Nostr public key."
.PD 0
.IP "\fBkind 9321\fR \- Nutzap event. Published by the sender, containing Cashu proofs P2PK\-locked to the recipient\*(Aqs specified public key. Includes the mint URL, unit, and optional event reference." 4
.IX Item "kind 9321 - Nutzap event. Published by the sender, containing Cashu proofs P2PK-locked to the recipient's specified public key. Includes the mint URL, unit, and optional event reference."
.ie n .IP "\fBkind 7376\fR \- Nutzap redemption history. Created when claiming tokens, tagging the original nutzap event(s) with a ""redeemed"" marker." 4
.el .IP "\fBkind 7376\fR \- Nutzap redemption history. Created when claiming tokens, tagging the original nutzap event(s) with a \f(CWredeemed\fR marker." 4
.IX Item "kind 7376 - Nutzap redemption history. Created when claiming tokens, tagging the original nutzap event(s) with a redeemed marker."
.PD
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Nutzap\->new(%fields);
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Nutzap\*(C'\fR object. Typically returned by
"from_event"; calling \f(CW\*(C`new\*(C'\fR directly is useful for testing or
manual construction.
.PP
.Vb 6
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Nutzap\->new(
\&        mint_url  => \*(Aqhttps://mint1\*(Aq,
\&        unit      => \*(Aqsat\*(Aq,
\&        recipient => $hex_pubkey,
\&        proofs    => [],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Accepted fields: \f(CW\*(C`relays\*(C'\fR (defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR), \f(CW\*(C`mints\*(C'\fR (defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR),
\&\f(CW\*(C`p2pk_pubkey\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`proofs\*(C'\fR (defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR), \f(CW\*(C`mint_url\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`unit\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`recipient\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`event_id\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`event_kind\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`nutzap_ids\*(C'\fR (defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR),
\&\f(CW\*(C`sender_pubkey\*(C'\fR. Croaks on unknown arguments.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS info_event
.IX Subsection "info_event"
.Vb 6
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Nutzap\->info_event(
\&        pubkey      => $hex_pubkey,
\&        relays      => [\*(Aqwss://relay1\*(Aq],
\&        mints       => [{ url => \*(Aqhttps://mint1\*(Aq, units => [\*(Aqsat\*(Aq] }],
\&        p2pk_pubkey => $hex_p2pk_key,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 10019 nutzap informational Net::Nostr::Event.
\&\f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`relays\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`mints\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`p2pk_pubkey\*(C'\fR are required. Each
mint entry is a hashref with \f(CW\*(C`url\*(C'\fR and an optional \f(CW\*(C`units\*(C'\fR arrayref
of supported base units (e.g. \f(CW\*(C`sat\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`usd\*(C'\fR).
.SS nutzap
.IX Subsection "nutzap"
.Vb 11
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Nutzap\->nutzap(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,        # required
\&        recipient  => $hex_pubkey,        # required (p tag)
\&        proofs     => [$proof_json, ...], # required (proof tags)
\&        mint_url   => \*(Aqhttps://mint\*(Aq,     # required (u tag)
\&        unit       => \*(Aqsat\*(Aq,              # optional, default \*(Aqsat\*(Aq
\&        event_id   => $hex_event_id,      # optional (e tag)
\&        event_kind => \*(Aq1\*(Aq,                # optional (k tag)
\&        relay_hint => \*(Aqwss://relay\*(Aq,      # optional
\&        content    => \*(Aqnice!\*(Aq,            # optional comment
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 9321 nutzap Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`recipient\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`proofs\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`mint_url\*(C'\fR are required. Multiple proofs create multiple
\&\f(CW\*(C`proof\*(C'\fR tags.
.SS redemption
.IX Subsection "redemption"
.Vb 7
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Nutzap\->redemption(
\&        pubkey        => $hex_pubkey,
\&        nutzap_ids    => [$event_id, ...],
\&        sender_pubkey => $hex_pubkey,
\&        relay_hint    => \*(Aqwss://relay\*(Aq,     # optional
\&        content       => $encrypted,        # optional (NIP\-44 encrypted)
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 7376 redemption Net::Nostr::Event. Multiple nutzap IDs
can be tagged in a single redemption. Each \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag includes the
\&\f(CW\*(C`redeemed\*(C'\fR marker.
.PP
The \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR parameter accepts pre\-encrypted NIP\-44 data containing
the redemption details (direction, amount, unit, created token reference).
Defaults to empty string if not provided.
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Nutzap\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 10019, 9321, or 7376 event into a \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Nutzap\*(C'\fR
object. Returns \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR for unrecognized kinds.
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::Nutzap\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates a nutzap\-related event. Croaks on invalid structure.
.PP
For kind 10019: requires at least one \f(CW\*(C`relay\*(C'\fR tag, one \f(CW\*(C`mint\*(C'\fR tag, and
a \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR tag.
.PP
For kind 9321: requires at least one \f(CW\*(C`proof\*(C'\fR tag, a \f(CW\*(C`u\*(C'\fR tag (mint URL),
and a \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag (recipient).
.PP
For kind 7376: requires at least one \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag.
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
Available on objects returned by "from_event". Which accessors contain
data depends on the event kind parsed.
.SS relays
.IX Subsection "relays"
Arrayref of relay URLs (kind 10019).
.SS mints
.IX Subsection "mints"
Arrayref of hashrefs with \f(CW\*(C`url\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`units\*(C'\fR keys (kind 10019).
.SS p2pk_pubkey
.IX Subsection "p2pk_pubkey"
The P2PK public key for receiving nutzaps (kind 10019).
.SS proofs
.IX Subsection "proofs"
Arrayref of proof JSON strings (kind 9321).
.SS mint_url
.IX Subsection "mint_url"
The mint URL from the \f(CW\*(C`u\*(C'\fR tag (kind 9321).
.SS unit
.IX Subsection "unit"
The base unit (kind 9321), e.g. \f(CW\*(C`sat\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`usd\*(C'\fR.
.SS recipient
.IX Subsection "recipient"
The recipient\*(Aqs Nostr pubkey from the \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag (kind 9321).
.SS event_id
.IX Subsection "event_id"
The nutzapped event ID from the \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag (kind 9321), or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS event_kind
.IX Subsection "event_kind"
The nutzapped event kind from the \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag (kind 9321), or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS nutzap_ids
.IX Subsection "nutzap_ids"
Arrayref of redeemed nutzap event IDs (kind 7376).
.SS sender_pubkey
.IX Subsection "sender_pubkey"
The nutzap sender\*(Aqs pubkey from the \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag (kind 7376).
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.IX Header "SEE ALSO"
NIP\-61 <https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/61.md>,
